  "description": [
    "OH Id Jamacian To Enter Dunbar Hi Dave Albritton the redoubtable high jumper who looks forward to another Olympics has used his influence to aid a young Jamaican to win a scholarship to come to this country for his schooling The youthful track star Louis A Gooden Jr will attend the Dun bar high school and then will be eligible to continue his education at Ohio State or any other uni versity in this state Louis A Gooden Sr father of the youthful sprinter was the Jamaican sprint champion of two decades ago He won many tro phies in his career and he prom ised himself that he would train his eldest son the ancient art of foot racing Louis Jr is the pro duct of that promise At Womers Boys school the lad has excelled in all events in which he has par ticipated His times for the cen tury and the 220 are 106 seconds and 233 seconds respectively For the age of the boy these times are short of phenomenal Albritton wlio was responsible for getting the scholarship along With J V Taffe is doing a splen did job with the Dunbar high school track team He"
  ],
